simcrs
------------------------------------------
SimCRS aims at providing a clean API and a simple implementation, as a C++
library, of a Travel-oriented Distribution System. It corresponds to the
simulated version of the real-world Computerized Reservation Systems (CRS).

SimCRS makes an extensive use of existing open-source libraries for increased
functionality, speed and accuracy. In particular the Boost (C++ Standard
Extensions: http://www.boost.org) library is used.

SimCRS is the one of the components of the Travel Market Simulator
(http://www.travel-market-simulator). However, it may be used in a stand-alone
mode.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.3.39-2
  cygwin-2.2.0-1
  libairinv1.00-1.00.1-1bl1
  libairtsp1.01-1.01.1-1bl1
  libboost_program_options1.57-1.57.0-1
  libgcc1-4.9.3-1
  libsimcrs-devel-1.01.1-1bl1
  libsimcrs1.01-1.01.1-1bl1
  libsimfqt1.00-1.00.1-1bl1
  libstdair1.00-1.00.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-4.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-2
  cmake-3.1.2-1
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.3-1
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.simcrs.org/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/simcrs/simcrs-1.01.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack simcrs-1.01.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./simcrs-1.01.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/simcrs-1.01.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/simcrs-1.01.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsimcrs1.01-1.01.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsimcrs-devel-1.01.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

